{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d3ed4516-44b1-4535-8a71-9c9296fbde32","content":"\n\nIn .NET MAUI, you configure platform lifecycle events in `CreateMauiApp()` using `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity => { /* app pausing */ })\n        .OnStop(activity => { /* app stopped */ }));\n#endif\n\n#if IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* entered background */ }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;`\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#if IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code conditional.\n- Each platform exposes its native events (e.g., `OnResume`, `OnDestroy` on Android; `WillEnterForeground`, `WillTerminate` on iOS).\n- All handlers are registered in **MauiProgram.cs** — no need to subclass platform `Activity` or `AppDelegate`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ee22baab-071f-4904-ba29-a2af96a9b865","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's `OnPause`/`OnStop` and iOS's `DidEnterBackground`. This is a general knowledge question, not a code task in the repo.","outputTokens":361},"id":"ca617896-c744-4ce9-a421-211331581814","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:49:26.427Z","parentId":"88aeb9b4-33a1-4e56-92c1-06c63d5b0bb8"}
